01:00:44.440 --> 01:00:45.860
Forward slash, I think.

01:00:45.860 --> 01:00:46.060
Yeah.

01:00:46.060 --> 01:00:50.340
That demarcates the end of positional-only arguments.

01:00:50.340 --> 01:00:53.500
So everything past that will be keywords or positional.

01:00:53.500 --> 01:00:57.060
And then as soon as you have the asterisk by itself, that denotes keyword-only.

01:00:57.060 --> 01:01:04.560
I think that's going to be really nice because it's going to deal with some annoying code where you actually do not care about that keyword name.

01:01:04.560 --> 01:01:05.660
